    "narrative": "The Austin Waves lineup today leans heavily into favorable platoon dynamics and park factors to navigate a slate containing several elite arms. The premier play is **Kyle Tucker** (76.51), who benefits from a favorable matchup against Colin Rea and wind conditions blowing out, amplifying his elite base projection. **Jackson Merrill** (70.76) and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (70.45) also profile as top-tier starts; **Jackson Merrill** leverages a significant platoon advantage against the right-handed Gallen, while **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** retains high efficiency despite the matchup against Cantillo due to his strong underlying xwOBA. **Miguel Vargas** (60.21) and **Andy Pages** (60.94) round out our most reliable options, with **Andy Pages** specifically boosted by a 5% wind-out factor and favorable SP Skill metrics.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision involved **Marcell Ozuna** (48.31), who narrowly missed the cut behind **Dominic Smith** (41.10). While **Marcell Ozuna** possesses a higher raw power ceiling, the optimizer favored **Dominic Smith** due to the specific combination of his BvP historicals against Zack Wheeler and the positional flexibility required to balance the roster. Conversely, we are exercising extreme caution with **Drake Baldwin** and **Dominic Smith**, as both face the formidable Zack Wheeler; their scores are tethered to \"Lineup Pending\" status, and their sub-50 efficiency ratings reflect the high risk of elite-tier pitching suppression. Owners should monitor the status of **Gunnar Henderson**, whose aggressive play against the difficult Crochet is buoyed by a +16% park factor, though his sub-20% SP Skill penalty serves as a stark reminder of the volatility inherent in today\u2019s matchup.",
